  "text": "The relativistic theory of cosmological perturbations is an essential tool to analyze cosmological data such as the Cosmic Microwave Background (CMB) anisotropies, and thus to connect the scenarios of the early universe, such as inflation, to cosmological observations. Because the temperature anisotropies of the CMB are so small (δT /T ∼ 10 −5 ), considering only linear perturbations is an excellent approximation. This is why most of the efforts devoted to the theory of cosmological perturbations have dealt with linear perturbations [1, 2, 3, [CITATION_1] .",
